Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.72,0:00:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that had happened, now seems to be \Nbut a test from the contriving minx, which is fate. {/mischievous/evil test}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.23,0:00:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A few words left unsaid, a tiny misunderstanding unsolved \Nand the entire family ends up being torn apart once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.73,0:00:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The day Lotte was supposed to return to Munich, \Nthe two pleaded with their father:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.82,0:00:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,"There's only one thing that we want.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.52,0:00:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.22,0:00:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,For us all to live together, \Nas a family of four."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.57,0:00:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to marry you, Luiselotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.25,0:00:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.48,0:00:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you who I need.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.07,0:00:51.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I do. And our children do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.20,0:00:59.21,Sign,,0,0,130,,{\c&HBAF0F1&\bord0\blur0.8\fs25}Episode 28 \N {\fs55}  Best Birthday Ever {最高の誕生日} \N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.85,0:01:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're already...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.85,0:01:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. It's true that I had proposed a marriage \Nto Frau Irene Gerlach.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.23,0:01:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,However, last night...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.83,0:01:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As the parting with Lotte was drawing near, \Nit dawned upon me for the first time. {lit is "when I had no choice but to part with lotte"}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.16,0:01:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,If I marry Frau Irene,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.13,0:01:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forgive myself for it. {/I can't marry ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.36,0:01:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I had been inconceivably wrong. {/made a big mistake}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.41,0:01:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So first thing in the morning, \NI headed for her house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.65,0:01:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I went there to revoke our engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.68,0:01:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, suddenly, the tables have turned,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.71,0:01:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,when she was actually the one \Nwho initiated the cancellation of engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.23,0:01:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She did that in response to me giving her \Na cold shoulder the day before. {irresponsible; perfunctory; careless feelings}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.96,0:01:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Unknowingly, I mistreated her.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.03,0:01:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief Bernau is a hearty guy, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.84,0:02:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you marry him, there would hardly be \Na single rainy day in your life. {/he is the one who can make you happy if ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:06.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And I know, he'd dote on Lotte as much as I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.74,0:02:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When returning to Vienna last time, I thought I'd send you \Nand Editor Bernau my heartfelt congratulations for wedding. {celebration (of a joyous occasion); blessing; giving one's blessing; wishing (someone) good luck}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.19,0:02:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, these girls opened my eyes to the truth: {/I was told by ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.52,0:02:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no use trying to trick my own heart into feeling so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.62,0:02:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It might be terribly late for that now, but still, \NI'd like to tell you, with all due candor, just how I feel. {honest; frank; candid; straightforward feelings}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.24,0:02:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I still love you even to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.70,0:02:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to marry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.04,0:02:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom! You should answer something to dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.48,0:02:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By being excessively vain in the distant past, \NI myself brought this about - {lit: long ago, I used to only think about myself}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.55,0:02:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to you, to Luise, and to Lotte,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.55,0:02:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I have delivered long years of suffering. {/painful thoughts - unsure if she means she had ... or give ... to them}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.92,0:03:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that... Was the same on my side.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.17,0:03:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I must...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.67,0:03:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,apologize to you for one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.41,0:03:12.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By saying that I'm about to marry Editor Bernau, \NI lied once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.67,0:03:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.58,0:03:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If only you would permit another chance for me, \NI'd like to try living together once more, {to give (esp. to someone of lower status); to bestow; to grant; to confer; to present; to award}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.42,0:03:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,as a family of four.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.42,0:03:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Luiselotte...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.27,0:03:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, we did it! Did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.60,0:03:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy! Love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.68,0:03:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers, dad. \NI'm so happy for us all!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.61,0:03:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheers, mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.54,0:04:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This means we four are living together now!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.62,0:04:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Forever, forever, fore-ver!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.03,0:04:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. All the way until you two \Nwalk down the aisle yourselves. {to marry (of a woman); to become a bride; to marry into (a family)​}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.07,0:04:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I really feel that I won't need \Na birthday present ever again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.88,0:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So do I! From now on, \NI'll do fine without Christmas presents, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.38,0:04:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This year, next year, and every year!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.23,0:04:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They're a good match, don't you think? \NThose dad and mom of ours! {well-matched (esp. of a couple); becoming; suitable}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.78,0:04:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.92,0:04:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, shouldn't we raise a toast to this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.36,0:04:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You're welcome to my flat if you'd like that. \NI owe you a feast, seven years' worth of them. {/cook/make}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.10,0:04:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.47,0:04:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These children are something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.87,0:04:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, they took that from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.63,0:04:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's from you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.00,0:04:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's from you, admit it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.89,0:05:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Been a long time!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.13,0:05:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.49,0:05:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you up to, skipping school?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.36,0:05:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie! And with you, Maria and Miria.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.27,0:05:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Not even denying you're playing hooky? {so (I take it that ...); then ...; so then​upon realizing something}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.08,0:05:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, right! It's plain to see now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.94,0:05:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We should whistle-blow it to the teacher, Annie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.46,0:05:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you whistle-blowing it to?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.87,0:05:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try to mess with Lotte, \NI'll come to deal with you personally. {/say bad things to}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.29,0:05:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte is two!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.51,0:05:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Luise. Even if some mere days ago I was still Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.33,0:05:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise is my big sister. {she says onesan, I dunno if they figured out who was born first somehow, or she just uses it in humorgous sense, like "guardian/sempai"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.12,0:05:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm... {lit is with me and I've not a single clue what's impled here}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.09,0:05:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,My meeker, but no smaller sister. {again, lit is "they call me sibling" and I don't understand the jist of this conversation, even if I sense a joke afoot}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.22,0:05:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Together, we switched places some while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.40,0:05:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, Luise, show the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.26,0:05:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's this guy! \NHe had been swinging the stick at the recent concert.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.62,0:06:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Pa... Par... Pap...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.31,0:06:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Palfy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.41,0:06:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.75,0:06:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Annie. Since explaining the whole story \Nwould take too long, let's do it some other time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.42,0:06:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, some other time, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.40,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you understand anything, Frau Annie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.56,0:06:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet she didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.67,0:06:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, as we move there, \Nyou'll have to change schools, too. {/I should start arranging your transfer into another school at once.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're probably feeling sad \Nabout parting with your friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.67,0:06:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I'll have to say goodbye to everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.02,0:06:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To teacher Linnekogel, to Ilse Merck, \Nto Annie, Maria and Miria.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.47,0:06:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Even parting with Annie and her goons \Nis somehow saddening. {to miss someone; to miss something; to feel lonely}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.02,0:06:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, the people who taught you to cook...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.96,0:06:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Butcher Herr Huber.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.45,0:06:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And grocery store owner Frau Wagenthaler.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And the piano teacher Leitner, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.00,0:07:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! How could I forget!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.27,0:07:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.94,0:07:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.89,0:07:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Editor-in-Chief Bernau.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.61,0:07:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We should definitely drop by \Nto say our goodbyes to Editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.71,0:07:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good point.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.11,0:07:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Editor-in-Chief Bernau \Nhad always been a good and faithful friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.65,0:07:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And he'll remain one forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.32,0:07:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, what about your job?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.66,0:07:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll find myself a new job in Vienna.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.16,0:07:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Staying home, doing whole lot of nothing \Nis not in my nature. {/not befitting/doesn't suit}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.16,0:07:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,For housekeeping, we already have Resi. \NNaturally, that doesn't mean we can't help her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be sure to!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.79,0:07:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.61,0:07:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It means parting with this flat as well, Lotte. {/room}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.61,0:07:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.59,0:07:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for all the memories we made here. {lit is "for the long time" but idk what that means}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.42,0:08:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye, Munich.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.09,0:08:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But also...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.60,0:08:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, Vienna!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.40,0:08:14.34,Sign,,0,0,0,,Vienna
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.82,0:08:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello, our new life.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.03,0:08:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you explain in simple terms, \Nwho is the newcomer?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.22,0:08:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.96,0:08:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,In short, she was the one who attended this place \Nunder Luise's name since the end of summer vacations.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.03,0:08:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know what to make of it. {no clue, sticking to deepl: "I'm not sure what's going on there"}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.90,0:08:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm getting it right, you had two twins, one of which \Nwas attending this school, and now the other one joins her?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.21,0:08:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Well, to put it simply, it's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.19,0:09:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... Still, what a puzzle. \NOh, and how could they be so similar, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.42,0:09:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed. At this rate, we'll have no choice, \Nbut to stick name tags on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.07,0:09:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm starting, Truda!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.33,0:09:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Next is you, Margarete!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.50,0:09:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's up, Truda?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.61,0:09:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe it? \NLotte is now also going to this school!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.70,0:09:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, our dad and mom \Nnow live together again!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know all the details \Nsometime later!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.59,0:09:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey-hey, Truda.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.09,0:09:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why am I seeing two Luises?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.40,0:09:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.76,0:09:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see! There really was more to it \Nthan meets the eye! {I would assume she means "I suspected they switched places" but really don't know, this doesn't feel right, so I'd just include a throwback to some memorable line from the beginning of the series}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.90,0:09:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet, people would start confusing them again. {lit: again, complicated; complex; intricate; confusing; difficult; troublesome things would occur - no clue what she means, maybe "people would confuse them again"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.60,0:09:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! I must let Christine know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.08,0:09:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And Stephie, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.09,0:09:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Truda! What's going on? \NWill you ever explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.14,0:09:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.79,0:10:09.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,{Friday - too lazy to make a sign for one word which doesn't matter all that much}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.55,0:10:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.91,0:10:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Enthralling play! {to listen to in an ecstasy}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.04,0:10:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, impressive indeed. \NIt seems, I should be the one learning from Lotte now. {/I'm no longer a match for lotte}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.98,0:10:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, Little Herrin Pianist.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.33,0:10:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Cake that's as refined as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.92,0:10:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! Sachertorte, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.42,0:10:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The yummiest cake in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.21,0:10:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,About your birthday tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.74,0:10:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Told you, don't bother with presents.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.36,0:11:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already received ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.53,0:11:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What better present one can get \Nthan living together as a family of four?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.75,0:11:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So the matter is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.86,0:11:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll need you two to lend me \Na few hours of your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.52,0:11:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? {\i1}Our time?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.90,0:11:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, tomorrow, we're going to the registry office \Nto hold the official ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.53,0:11:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Marriage ceremony, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.70,0:11:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,All that on our birthday?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.39,0:11:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We'll do it tomorrow, \Nwhatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.97,0:11:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, there wouldn't have been any remarriage \Nif not for Luise and Lotte's intense arbitration.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Every year, starting now, together with your birthday, \Nwe'll also celebrate the second birthday of our feelings. {lit: from now on, every year, every time we celebrate your birthday, I want to refresh/renew my feelings - not a fudckung clue what's this about, really not a single one - 誕生日を祝うたびに気持ちを新たにしたいの - how is that related to previous or to next line or to common sense? how is marrying on their birthday help you refresh the feelings? why every time you celebrate? why so specific, why it's not enough to just say "your every birthday"? why it wouldn't be refreshing to split those days and celebrate them separately?; I see that iwai can be "congratulatory gift; present" so maybe it's "you/I'll get feelings renewed as ... present"}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.85,0:11:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.71,0:11:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Most naturally!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.78,0:11:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Fantastic! This way, we'll make our birthday \Nthe day of our parents' wedding as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.15,0:11:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As a matter of fact, Editor-in-Chief Bernau \Nalso promised to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.47,0:11:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ditto for Doctor Strobl \Nand Herr Gabele, the painter.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.60,0:11:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Sublime! This spells "great day" already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.20,0:11:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Best birthday ever!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I so can't wait for tomorrow to come!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.41,0:12:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, mom! Hurry, hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.55,0:12:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Still too soon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.29,0:12:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Doctor Strobl.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.32,0:12:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.29,0:12:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My, is that a beaming of happiness \NI'm seeing on your faces? {/happy aren't yoy}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.24,0:12:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes! Absolutely! {/very much}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.94,0:12:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans! You managed to come, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.91,0:12:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I already know the whole story. \NCongratulations, so you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lotte. This one is the true Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.62,0:12:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, in this quality, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.69,0:12:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys sure are miracle-makers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.60,0:12:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everyone can bring \Nhis divorced parents to reconciliation!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.56,0:13:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn well said. From myself, though, I'd like to add: \NI gave you an inch and you took a mile. {no clue: although I would say, you went a bit overboard/did a little unnecessary thing/went a little bit the extra mile - maybe he means "you made my efforts towards your mom vain" or maybe "you made me come all the way here" or "you went further and not just made them reconcile but made them marry too" or }
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.62,0:13:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you suppose I should run Munich Graph \Nwith our main scooper enticed by you? {hope its 敏腕記者 but still not sure what to make of it, probably something around "shrewd/persistent reporter who knows how to get to the bottom of anything"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.91,0:13:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange, we supplied you \Nwith a first-class correspondent in Vienna! {/in exchange, an excellent (special) correspondent (e.g. for a newspaper) in vienna was born}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.37,0:13:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. At least we didn't yield her to any rival company. {/if she went to rival, we'd be in trouble}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.47,0:13:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,No way I let some odious bunch \Nget their hands on a staff so valuable. {unsure what he means, will she keep working for MG from vienna? lit is "to the very end; to the last; thoroughly; completely; fully​, for the sake of our company, I'll get her to work"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you! That's exactly what I love \Nthe most about you, Editor-in-Chief Bernau!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.62,0:13:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But say, Herr Editor, \Nwon't you miss her personally as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.28,0:13:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! I'm not too happy \Nabout losing "a thorn in my side" either. {/fighting buddy}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.61,0:13:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe something else? {I think she means "you regard her in that way only [and not also as someone you loved?]"}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you getting at, Fraulein Shrewd? {precocity (esp. of a young girl); acting grown up} {/want to say}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.88,0:13:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, all aboard. {/ride}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.53,0:13:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't go, Peperl!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.92,0:13:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess there's no helping it. \NLet him come along, too. {/well it's fine, let's bring him along}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,My heartfelt congratulations, Frau. {/frau mistress/herrin}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.07,0:13:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Now, would you please \Nfinish the party preparations?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.97,0:13:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.01,0:13:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back safely.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.24,0:13:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, the bride's carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.25,0:13:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Miss Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.32,0:13:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Editor-in-Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.35,0:14:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, right. This morning, someone entrusted me this.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.18,0:14:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Munich Graph cover!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.11,0:14:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Our photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.52,0:14:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, why did this happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.02,0:14:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I was planning to surprise Lotte and everyone \Non a better occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.23,0:14:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd betray me like that? {/do extra/unnecessary thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was from some pretty woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.07,0:14:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,She also asked me to pass to Herr Palfy and his wife \Nher best wishes for the wedding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.81,0:14:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So it was her...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.15,0:14:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Palfy, I don't consider myself a loser. {lit is "I won't lose" so either she can't make up her mind or there's a hidden meaning to this all}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.96,0:14:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be happier this way, \Nbut so will I, and by several orders more. {lit is "I'm going to be happier than all of you." and idk why she'd be suddenly so harsh and cruel, or what she means to say}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.53,0:14:57.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,{ウィーン第一区 戸籍役場} Vienna First District Family Registry Office
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.74,0:15:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then... Frau Luiselotte Körner
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.24,0:15:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and Herr Ludwig Palfy...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, and now I would ask you
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to sign this marriage certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.73,0:15:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish we could see it one day, \Nmom wearing her real wedding dress. {unsure, maybe she means "mom is not wearing a real/genuine ..." or "this ... is disappointing" or "we never got a chance to ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.91,0:15:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But don't be too greedy in your wishes! {lit is "don't say to live in luxury; to indulge oneself" I think she means "don't get cocky/what you got is already rare enough/don't get used to such a chance" but really unsure, deepl: But I can't afford the luxury./it's not a luxury}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.45,0:15:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Attending their own parents' wedding ceremony - \Nnot many children get that kind of luxury!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.67,0:15:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's true as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.44,0:15:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the ceremony is concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.13,0:15:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a happy marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.21,0:15:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, Luise, starting today, \Nwe're officially a family again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.55,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.62,0:15:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, mom
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.33,0:15:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.26,0:16:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.30,0:16:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Your left hand, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.41,0:16:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the magical ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.08,0:16:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's unseen to the eye, but with magic, \Nthis ring protects its wearer at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.46,0:16:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The two rings are connected \Nwith a thin thread, invisible as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.59,0:16:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Two persons wearing those can never take them off \Nand are bound to love each other until the end of times.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In times of abundance, \Nand in times of need... {lit: when rich; wealthy​, and when poor; needy}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.93,0:16:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in good health, \Nand when bedridden... {vigorous; healthy; sound ... sick; ill; ailing}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.32,0:16:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, Luise...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.22,0:16:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.88,0:17:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, you repay magic with even more magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.86,0:17:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, welcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.39,0:17:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Good morning, Herr Gabele!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.93,0:17:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you said you wanted to show to us all?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.96,0:17:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This something is ought \N to exhilarate you both, I reckon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.96,0:17:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If anything, it was enough to compel me \Nto bid my farewells to this place, starting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.20,0:17:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Herr Gabele, you're moving out of here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.31,0:17:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what's the use of talking? Come on in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What exactly is happening here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.23,0:18:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How come dad's piano is in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.05,0:18:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We heeded to Lotte's suggestion and acted on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I negotiated an exchange of rooms with Herr Gabele.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.57,0:18:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? So Herr Gabele \Nbiding farewell to it just means...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.57,0:18:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, from now on, \Nyou'll be working right next to us, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.62,0:18:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's about time I get rid of that old habit \Nof not showing up at home for weeks on end. {/there won't be the cases of not coming home for god knows how many days, like in the old times}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.02,0:18:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And my new atelier is a garden of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.82,0:18:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,By your courtesy, I can now work to my heart's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.95,0:18:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So here is my late present to Lotte and Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte! Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.22,0:18:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to be late for school!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.54,0:18:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, your notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.85,0:18:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.45,0:19:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess there's no reeducating dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Mom! There's no second earring!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.92,0:19:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Gosh, I left it upstairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.89,0:19:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I'll be late for the interview! {gathering material (for an article, novel, etc.); collecting information; covering (an event, incident, etc.); reporting; interview (for a news story)}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.76,0:19:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,We're off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.42,0:19:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.39,0:19:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm off!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.99,0:19:19.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care, Frau!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.35,0:19:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Granted at last, Luise and Lotte's wish. {/dream came true}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.72,0:19:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole family lives together again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.83,0:19:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What started as a tenuous conspiracy - \Nthe adventure of the two had arrived to a happy ending. {/having started in secretly; in secret; unseen; unobserved; inwardly; in private, ... ended safely}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.17,0:20:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,However, nobody can say for sure \Nif the true adventure is not just merely starting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.74,0:20:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't we sneak a wee peek
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.01,0:20:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,into the new everyday routine of the Palfy family?
Comment: 0,0:20:20.62,0:20:20.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.56,0:20:30.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.09,0:20:33.55,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.55,0:20:37.27,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.27,0:20:40.18,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.40,0:20:51.82,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.82,0:20:55.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.58,0:20:59.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.12,0:21:02.52,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:05.69,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.54,0:21:09.09,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.09,0:21:13.64,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.64,0:21:17.79,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:22.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.99,0:21:26.40,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams - {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.40,0:21:30.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.03,0:21:32.80,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.85,0:21:37.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.62,0:21:41.03,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, my duty is to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:44.62,0:21:44.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.81,0:21:46.28,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.25,0:21:53.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, dad had proposed a trip \Nto his uncle's villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.46,0:21:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,A wonderful place in the countryside, \Nsurrounded by nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.92,0:21:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful! Our first family trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.72,0:22:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad said "It can't wait," didn't he? {no clue what she's about}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.22,0:22:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.89,0:22:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's very dad-like, but I'm still a little worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.63,0:22:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Lotte? Why are you worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.44,0:22:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Final episode of I and Myself:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.81,0:22:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Our First Family Trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.34,0:22:14.24,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 29 \NOur First Family Trip {初めての家族旅行}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.07,0:22:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Meet you there!{\i0}
